This paper deals with modeling and analyzing multicast device-to-device (D2D) transmission, which is a topic related to network protocols and communication technologies. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves mathematical modeling and optimization, which suggests that it could belong to cs.IT (Information Theory) or cs.SY (Systems and Control). Additionally, the paper discusses metrics related to multimedia transmission, which could place it in cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper examines the impact of network dynamics and assistance, which could relate to cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing).
